                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="423962" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 21:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. In fact the only reason for LNET_PING_BUFFER_MAX is that currently IB RDMA doesn&apos;t support IPv6 addresses. Otherwise we could do way more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="423725" author="adilger" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 01:20:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=simmonsja&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;simmonsja&quot;&gt;simmonsja&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hornc&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hornc&quot;&gt;hornc&lt;/a&gt;, I thought there was just recently patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/54673&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/54673&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17700&quot; title=&quot;lnet ping: failed to ping NID: Protocol error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17700&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17700&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: properly calculate ping buffer size&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that was changing the limit of the number of NIDs in a ping reply because of IPv6?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;tt&gt;LNET_PING_BUFFER_MAX = 3960&lt;/tt&gt; it should be possible to receive up to 198 IPv6 NIDs or 495 IPv4 NIDs, so I think this ticket can be closed as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10003&quot; title=&quot;lnetctl error &amp;quot;cannot add network: invalid argument&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10003&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10003&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or similar?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
